This is my dear friend @thine_queen_tut and I am so angry to say that I have witnessed medical racism try to end her life. Please swipe through and hear her story & SHARE it as this is something black women constantly have to face. 
Shae is one of the most hardworking, loving and intelligent people I know- but most importantly she is a human being deserving of respect, dignity and doctors who can show EMPATHY. After dealing with unsanitary/inhumane conditions at Wyckoff heights hospital I took her to @bkmethodist.em & I was hoping that since I was there I could help advocate and show them that she isn’t lying or exaggerating- my friend was sick and needed treatment. We were met by Nicole Quattrocchi, she had seen shae earlier and said she just had acid reflux- after discharging Shae immediately fainted outside the hospital. Since this doctor misdiagnosed her the first time, Shae just asked to see another doctor and instead Nicole handed us discharge papers and told my sick friend to see a psychiatrist. I was begging Nicole and another doctor Michael Polito to please listen and they told me Shae just had anxiety. I told them I’ve had anxiety since I was 13 and that never led to blood in my stool, fainting, losing consciousness or no control of bodily functions. Michael replied by telling me that the hospital was for “real patients only.” When we told them they would be liable for the negligent harm they caused Nicole laughed in my face and said “O well I guess It’ll be a liability.” I begged them to please treat my friend and they responded by saying we both needed psychiatric help and called security. I told security my friend was sick and they tried to force us to a parking lot exit with stairs even after I said “she faints uncontrollably please help us” and I had to put my foot down and take her through an exit that was less dangerous. That night I spent it awake so I could watch my friend sleep- checking her vitals and breath every 10 mins to make sure she’s alive. Now her friends are taking shifts to care for her bc doctors refuse to do it- they say she’s perfectly fine but how the fuck is passing out repeatedly fine?

🌺Today is my 30th birthday🌺
Something I never thought I would get to say, but I’m so grateful to say it. I grew up in an extremely abusive household- one where my abuser attempted to m*rder me at 16 and encouraged my suicidal ideations. After running away at 17 I genuinely believed I would perish sooner rather than later. When I finally escaped, I spent years dealing with mental illness, self hatred and immense drug and alcohol use to numb my anger, sorrow and confusion : what identity did I have without my abuser? It was not easy but that hard internal work was worth every second. I want to be open about this bc I want anyone dealing with familial or romantic abuse to know, your happiness, your safety, your LIFE is worth it. Leave as soon as you can! I was told I was unloveable, I was a sickness that needed to be put down, I deserved to be abandoned and I would amount to nothing if I did not live a life of obedience as a servant to my abuser’s narcissism. I stand before you proving that all of that is a lie. By taking that leap of faith for me I was able to find my truth: I am love and I am loved deeply, I am worthy of joy, I am entitled to safety and respect, no one has possession over me and I am grateful to say that those I allow in my life have helped me grow into my potential as a woman, a friend and sister. I spent my 20s fighting to find and heal myself, I am so excited to spend my 30s enjoying the fruits of my labor. To anyone who has shown me love, helped me, shouted me out, supported me, know I am forever grateful and will never forget your kindness. 
I used to be ashamed of celebrating my self, today I replace that shame with pride and an adoration for the person I’m becoming, flaws and all. 
I’ve already received quite a gift, but if you feel inclined to send for a bday blunt my Venmo, Cashapp and PayPal are all in my bio ❤️

Dearest Tina,
Today when I learned of your passing, I let out a scream that was buried in the pits of my broken heart. I have loved you since I learned to speak, loved you since my mom got me my first ever cd- your album “Simply The Best.” I’ve loved you since my infancy and now as you soar and sing amongst the heavens I want to tell you why. My childhood was painful but some of my favorite memories are singing your songs with my mother, sister and cousins. I even dressed up as you for Halloween multiple times as a child because who could be better than the Queen Tina Turner? Even into my teenage years when I was suicidal and depressed, I could put on your music and dance in my bedroom. Suddenly I wasn’t this sad, shell of a kid, I was Tina- I was strong, powerful, confident and creative, for those minutes I would sing your songs there was nothing I could not do. As I got older I craved to know you better- I learned about your life, your hardships, your pain and your triumph. You were and will always be the Queen of Rock and Roll and to see this country, this entertainment industry make a mockery of your pain, your honesty, your power in the face of abuse made my blood boil. And even with all of that you prioritized your happiness and believed in yourself in a world that told you black girls should just be happy with the scraps we get. I thought of you when I finally ran away from home- I was 17 with nothing but a backpack, bruises and bloody bite marks on my face. I had nothing but when I was finally able to retrieve some items, I took my copy of Simply the Best and played it to remind myself that my safety, my happiness, my life was worth fighting for. The woman I am today refuses to tolerate abuse, the woman I am today prioritizes her happiness, the woman I am today does not settle when it comes to love because I deserve simply the best. The woman I am today was shaped by you Tina Turner, and not a day goes by where I am not eternally grateful for you and the blessings you’ve bestowed on us. Rest in Peace Tina Turner and if there’s ever anything you hear from me I hope it’s “thank you for everything, I love you.” 
#TinaTurner

Today my mother/abuser wrote to me to say that she discovered my past as a Pro D0mme. She was disgusted & appalled that I would pick a “talentless” profession- so much so that it makes her want to end her own life. The only response I had to that was laughter. This woman who claims to be pro black, pro queer, anti misogyny found it in herself to demonize me for doing sw- sw I did to survive and feed myself in a world that quite literally wanted me dead. She had the audacity to quote Audre Lorde and deem that she and my ancestors found what I did to be shameful, and I can’t help but laugh at that misplaced shame. People like her, people that crave power and control, hate swers bc swers defy every construct set in place by white supremacy. SW allows for those that have been habitually sexualized and controlled to take that power back and monetize it for THEMSELVES. SW is work and kink and BDSM are a staple in redefining social norms, discovering the limitlessness of the self and enforcing pleasure, communication and consent in a society that makes a profit off of shame and repression. I will always be open about my past work and the love I have for the SW community bc there is no reason for any shame or stigma to exist surrounding it. The very culture we have exists bc of swers, art and fashions have long been influenced by swer muses, and since the beginning those that choose to talk down to swers are the same ones that have no problem reaping the benefits of our services, culture, lingo, etc. My mother made a point to express her disgust, but didn’t have the words to express why she was disgusted but I already know why. Bc when she seems me now in all my glory, she no longer sees a person she can control. When she looks at Madame Namio she sees someone who is untouchable, someone who lives life by her own rules, someone who does not need need to adhere to the respectability politics of white supremacy in order to find self worth. No one, not even she, can fill me with shame bc I am already filled with pride over the work I have done and the work I will continue to do. I am powerful in my truth, can you say the same about yourself?

If my work and content ever spoke to you, if I’ve helped or soothed you in any way, please read this. The housing crisis in NYC has reached a peak level of danger and greed and it is about to claim me as its next victim. Due to this, antiblackness and a MAJOR betrayal/antiblackness from someone I considered family, I will be losing my home of 2 years after July 31st. Now I have a few weeks to find a new home and gather funds or I will become homeless again (I was homeless for years at the age of 17). I currently have 4 jobs, 2 of which I do from home so losing my home would mean absolute financial ruin. It would mean losing my dog who is the sole reason I have not just given into my suicidal ideations. It would mean my life, a life that I have worked so hard to create will crumble at my very fingertips. If you are in any place to donate I would be eternally grateful- every dollar will go towards securing housing & moving expenses. If you are able PLEASE share this! Eternally grateful to be celebrating 3 years of my love Platano Maduro! 3 years ago today I flew to Puerto Rico during the height of the COVID Pandemic to adopt sweet Platano. I never believed in love at first sight but that all changed the day @safeandsoundsatos sent me a photo of my perfect chunk. Now I cannot imagine my life without my sweet Platano- I love the way she wakes me up with kisses and her paws on my chest. I love the way she wiggles her whole butt when she’s happy or begging for a treat. I love her resilience and ability to love so sincerely even after experiencing horrific violence in her early youth. I love how ridiculous her barking and growling sounds and how she really be believing she is pit Bull sized. This dog is the reason I wake up in the morning, the reason I push myself to strive, the reason I don’t give up on myself- because giving up on me means giving up on her. Even after immense betrayal, heartbreak and racism almost shattered me into pieces this summer, Platano was there to put me back together. Here’s to many more years with my partner in crime, I wouldn’t want to share this life with anyone else❤️ #rescuedog #reacuedogsofinstagram #chiweenie #chiweeniesofinstagram #chiweenielove

2023 was a rollercoaster of emotions and a major test of strength~ I worked multiple jobs usually until 5/6AM, I ended an 8 yr relationship when I saw I was viewed as disposable, I almost faced homeless and had to find a place to live, work 4 jobs AND pack up an entire apartment alone bc my roommate decided to disappear, I left that apartment to move in with an INSANE roommate who was obsessed with Republican demon twinks, left cheese slices on the floor and endangered my life and those are just some pieces of the highlight reel. But amidst the muck I also got to travel to Colombia with some of my dearest friends, find a home with lovely people and a backyard for my dog, completely paid off my loan for Esthetician School and excelled at all of my professions. The biggest triumph of mine this year, was choosing myself each time I faced immense betrayal, abuse or harm. Instead of relishing in my anger and plotting vengeance, I chose to focus on my well being, on building a life for me and Platano, on bettering myself in the face of my adversary. Growing up in violence means being consumed by my anger is a cross I have to bear, but this year I chose to carry myself to success each time. Because I deserve better than the cards I was dealt and you cannot be your biggest critic without being your biggest supporter. I’m proud of the woman I became this year and I’m excited to see her reap the fruits of her labor in 2024.
